Changes to her ult make it impossible to do damage at a safe range. I don't see any niche for her anymore, and it's frankly not fun to play.
The baffling thing about this is that I don't think anyone was complaining that Anivia's ult was oppressive. Sure, she can kind of turtle games by just clearing at the base chokes- but this doesn't even fix that! The only thing the new ult is good for is static clearing.
I don't want to get super dramatic, but this rework is very discouraging and makes me feel like I've wasted my time playing this champ.


These changes are a nerf in 95% of cases, the exclusions being the ones where the enemy team forms a perfect little clump inside your ult for a full 3 seconds- in which case its actually pretty good. Her waveclear is awful unless you're boss at predicting minion movement, AND you have the mana to sustain the ult long enough for them to reach there. Disengaging and peeling has become extremely difficult and limited to single targets in most cases. Anivia's overall presence in teamfights has never felt less meaningful, at any point, in any meta (hey there swifties).
Riot's main idea for reworking champion is to give them both a clear identity, and more importantly, a reason to pick them above other champions of similar roles. Given her new skill floor, the disproportionate skewing of her risk/reward balance, and inconsistency of her teamfight presence, we have to ask ourselves this question:
Why WOULD we pick Anivia over any other control mage?
Riot's answer is slightly better CC that doesn't even come into effect until after Anivia is level 16+.

